#html 파일
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <title>HTML & CSS Basic Summary</title>
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com" />
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin />
    <link
      href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Fira+Sans:wght@400;700&family=Oswald:wght@700&family=Roboto:wght@400;900&display=swap"
      rel="stylesheet"
    />

    <link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css" />
  </head>
  <body>
    <header>
      <h1>HTML & CSS Basic Summary</h1>
      <img src="html-css.png" alt="HTML and CSS logos" />
    </header>
    <main>
      <h2>HTML Summary</h2>
      <p>
        HTML (HyperText Markup Language) is used to define our page contest,
        structure and meaning. You don't use it for styling purposes. Use CSS
        for that instead!
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>HTML uses "elements" to describe (annotate) contest</li>
        <li>
          HTML elements typically have an opening tag, contest and the a closing
        </li>
        <li>You can also have void (empty) elements with atributes</li>
        <li>
          There's long list of available elements but you'll gain experinece
          over time, no worries
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        Learn more about all available HTML elements on the
        <a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element"
          >MDN HTML element reference.</a
        >
      </p>
      <h2>CSS Summary</h2>
      <p>
        CSS (Cascading Styles Sheets) is used for styling your page contest.
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Styles are assigned via property-value pairs</li>
        <li>You can assign styles via the "styles" attribute</li>
        <li>
          To avoid code duplication, you typically use global styles (e.g.via
          the "style" element) instead
        </li>
        <li>
          a=Alternatively, you can work with external stylesheet files which you
          "link" to
        </li>
        <li>
          When working wih CSS, concepts link "inheritance", "specificity" and
          the "box model" should be understood.
        </li>
        <p>
          Learn more about all available CSS properties and values on the <a
            href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/Reference"
            >MDN CSS property reference.</a
          >
        </p>
      </ul>
    </main>
    <footer></footer>
  </body>
</html>
#css 파일
body {
    background-color: rgb(244, 234, 255) ;
    font-family: 'Roboto', sans-serif;  
}

h1{
    font-size:  52px;
    color:  rgb(88,49,196);
}

header {
    text-align: center;
    padding:  32px;
    
}

header img {
    width:  300px;

}
